    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> with your <strong>curry powder</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until warmed through and fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> curried</strong> <strong>chickpeas</strong> to the coronation<strong> </strong>mix and stir it all together – these are your<strong> creamy</strong> <strong>coronation chickpeas</strong></p>",
